<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-21T13:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-21T13:36:00-05:00" n="1289" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1289">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/5.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-21T12:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1912—noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s March 27, 5 p.m. Protests are being made here by
                            representatives of American taxpayers in the State of Chihuahua against
                            the collection attempted there by local authorities of certain mining
                            taxes already paid by them to the revolutionary government of Orozco,
                            which was the de facto government at the time of payment. I am to-day
                            instructing American Consul at Chihuahua to advise Americans in his
                            district to decline to pay taxes a second time.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>